@startuml
' Participants = only the application components you provided
participant "Visualization\n(Front-end)" as Visualization
participant "User Management\n(Auth / RBAC)" as UserManagement
participant "Automation\n(Rule Engine / Control)" as Automation
participant "Device Integration\n(PLC / Sensors)" as DeviceIntegration
participant "Event Detection\n(Anomaly / Fault)" as EventDetection
participant "Notification\n(Alerting / Escalation)" as Notification
participant "Logging\n(Audit / Historical)" as Logging
participant "Simulation\n(Virtual Factory / Predictive)" as Simulation

' --- User interacts with Visualization (front-end) — represented as external input to Visualization
note right of Visualization
  End users interact with the system through
  the Visualization component (web UI / dashboard).
end note

' 1. Login / Auth flow
Visualization -> UserManagement : Authenticate user (credentials / token)
UserManagement --> Visualization : Auth token / roles (200 OK)

' 2. User requests live dashboard / control or simulation
Visualization -> Automation : Request realtime state / execute control (with auth token)
activate Automation

' 3. Automation queries device state or issues control
Automation -> DeviceIntegration : Read sensor/state OR Send control command
activate DeviceIntegration
DeviceIntegration --> Automation : Ack / current device state
deactivate DeviceIntegration

' 4. Automation logs the action / event
Automation -> Logging : Persist event / command audit

' 5. Event detection pipeline (continuous or on data push)
Automation -> EventDetection : Push sensor data / state snapshot
activate EventDetection
EventDetection --> Automation : EventDetected? (anomaly/fault) / classification
deactivate EventDetection

' 6. If event/fault detected -> notifications and logging
alt event/fault detected
    Automation -> Notification : Create alert (with context)
    Notification -> Logging : Persist alert history
    Notification --> Automation : Alert delivery status
end

' 7. Visualization may request a simulation run (what-if / predictive)
Visualization -> Simulation : Request scenario simulation (params)
activate Simulation
Simulation -> Automation : Request model inputs / recent state
Automation --> Simulation : Provide state / model inputs
Simulation --> Visualization : Simulation results / predicted outcomes
deactivate Simulation

' 8. Automation may request simulation for predictive control
Automation -> Simulation : Ask for prediction / recommend action
Simulation --> Automation : Predicted outcome / suggested parameters

deactivate Automation
@enduml

